  "doc_id": "22514",
  "text": "Invasion assays were performed as described by Kieschnick et al [CITATION_1] and Sugi et al. [CITATION_2] Briefly, freshly harvested and purified parasites (1×10 5 ) were inoculated onto a monolayer of HFF cells on a coverslip for 1 h at 37°C with the different NP solutions (reconstituted in fresh medium prior to use) or medium only to serve as mock treatment. Following invasion, the cells were washed three times with ice-cold PBS, and extracellular parasites were stained with rabbit anti-T. gondii RH strain polyclonal antibodies (1:1,000) (Bio-Rad Laboratories, Hercules, CA, USA) in PBS containing 2% FCS for 30 min on ice. The cells were then washed three times with PBS containing 2% FCS, fixed with 4% paraformaldehyde in PBS, and permeabilized with ice-cold methanol for 20 min.",
